State of Connecticut v. Desmond Whyte (10619)

Dupont, C. J., Foti and Heiman, Js.

Argued March 26 decision released April 20, 1993 *905Mary Hadden and Earl I. Williams, for the appellant (defendant). David J. Sheldon, deputy assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Donald A. Browne, state’s attorney, and Kevin Dunn, deputy assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
